Mike Choe wrote:
&gt; hi all.
&gt; how can you define your own testing criteria in JUnit?
&gt; i think there&#39;s a way and i thought i read about it somewhere but i&#39;m
&gt; blanking out.

It depends what you mean by &quot;testing criteria&quot;.

You can extend the TestCase class to have additional assert methods if you
want to routinely check on different things. For example, I&#39;ve got a group
of class doing a fair bit of work with reflection. I ended up defining a new
test base class, and added a method like this:

public void assertType(Class expectedType, Object o) {
  assertNotNull(&quot;Can&#39;t really check the type of a null object&quot;, 0);
  assert(&quot;Expected type &lt;&quot; + expectedType.toString() + &quot;&gt;. Actual Type: &lt;&quot; +
o.getClass().toString() + &quot;&gt;&quot;,
         o instanceof expectedType);
}

Is this the sort of thing you mean?

Robert.

